--- !u!114 &8176257048539077146
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 2178389205546963609}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: a4007908f8dfb874baac36f5488767c6, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::BookInteractable
  bookText: 
  pages:
  - text: The radiation was coming from the dump yard because scientists had unknowingly
      been disposing of radioactive material there for years. They thought the waste
      was ordinary industrial material, so they buried it in sealed containers beneath
      the ground. Over time, some of the containers began to weaken, allowing radiation
      to leak into the surrounding soil and air.
    image: {fileID: 21300000, guid: abe89e832e8c67548b99854fc352f806, type: 3}
    images: []
  - text: "To prepare the potion against radiation, here are locations where to find
      them and gather them:\r\r\n"
    image: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 7dd012cfadfd05e46bad9b365f3027b5, type: 3}
    images: []
  - text: 'Aylostera: harmless red rose with no spikes, known for its pure and gentle
      nature.'
    image: {fileID: 0}
    images:
    - {fileID: 21300000, guid: af1f6e2d2c3c9c0408718d7ad584b7f4, type: 3}
    - {fileID: 21300000, guid: 67b8a21d79e8e4742ab27bd63d075b56, type: 3}
  - text: 'Coccineus: pink flower used as a symbol of protection and safety.'
    image: {fileID: 0}
    images:
    - {fileID: 21300000, guid: b50d0297f4b184d45b8eef84f4713b6c, type: 3}
    - {fileID: 21300000, guid: fb2e6de1a574fc6448f332b92b49691f, type: 3}
  - text: 'Mycena Radii Custos: rare mushroom believed to protect the body from radiation.'
    image: {fileID: 0}
    images:
    - {fileID: 21300000, guid: 8c32b913d07d57c478e7fc3768e54931, type: 3}
    - {fileID: 21300000, guid: dce9f8fabc5ae5b409a04330c9e7c284, type: 3}
  - text: "**Personal Diary of Dr. Arthur Hale**\r\n\r\n**March 15**\r\nBilly has
      always been a strange child.\r\nNot strange in a bad way. Curious. Imaginative.\r\nHe
      refuses to go near the old castle in the center of the forest. He says something
      watches him from the broken windows. Every time we pass it, he hides behind
      me and keeps his eyes on the ground.\r\nHe is also terrified of the house we
      live in. The same house he is afterwards playing in.\r\nHe claims the walls
      whisper at night.\r\nThe visitor's hut is even worse. He refuses to enter it
      unless I go first.\r\nAnd the toilets around the reserve... Billy says they
      smell so terrible that monsters must live inside them.\r\nI always laughed
      at these fears.\r\n\r\n**April 28**\r\nMy research is progressing faster than
      expected.\r\nRadiation levels remain stable according to my calculations.\r\nThe
      authorities abandoned this region years ago because they believed it was too
      dangerous. They were wrong.\r\nI know this place better than anyone.\r\nBilly
      and I can live here safely.\r\n\r\n**May 2**\r\nI was wrong.\r\nGod forgive
      me.\r\nI was wrong.\r\nAn underground pocket of concentrated radiation ruptured
      without warning.\r\nBilly was nearby when it happened.\r\nThe exposure should
      have killed him instantly.\r\nInstead, he survived.\r\n\r\n**May 10**\r\nThe
      changes have begun.\r\nHis arms are longer.\r\nHis bones are growing at impossible
      rates.\r\nHis skin feels hard and uneven.\r\nI tell him everything will be
      okay.\r\nHe believes me.\r\nI do not believe in myself.\r\n\r\n**May 22**\r\nBilly
      asked me today if he was becoming a monster.\r\nI couldn't answer.\r\nWhat
      kind of father can answer a question like that?\r\n\r\n**June 4**\r\nI can
      no longer stay near him.\r\nThe mutations have become unpredictable.\r\nWhen
      frightened, he loses control of his strength.\r\nYesterday he shattered a door
      without realizing it.\r\nHe cried afterward.\r\nHe did not mean to do it.\r\nHe
      is still Billy inside.\r\nBut his body is becoming something else.\r\nFor both
      our safety, I left him in the forest.\r\nIt was the hardest decision I have
      ever made.\r\nNow I monitor him from outside the contaminated zone.\r\nI watch
      from a distance.\r\nA father reduced to a spectator.\r\n\r\n**June 19**\r\nBilly
      has adapted to the forest.\r\nHe avoids places that frightened him before.\r\nThe
      old castle remains untouched.\r\nThe visitor's hut remains empty.\r\nEven now,
      after everything he has become, he still refuses to approach the toilets scattered
      around the reserve.\r\nI watched him smell one from nearly fifty meters away
      before running in the opposite direction.\r\nPart of me laughed.\r\nPart of
      me cried.\r\nBecause that tiny habit reminded me that somewhere beneath the
      mutations, my son still exists.\r\n\r\n**July 2**\r\nThe animals are gone.\r\nEvery
      last one of them.\r\nThe radiation killed the ecosystem days ago.\r\nBilly
      has nothing left to hunt.\r\nHis hunger is becoming unbearable.\r\nI can see
      him growing weaker.\r\nMore desperate.\r\nMore aggressive.\r\n\r\n**July 11**\r\nToday
      I discovered something remarkable.\r\nHidden among old research documents was
      a formula.\r\nA serum capable of protecting humans from radiation exposure
      forever once it is made.\r\nA cure? No.\r\nBut a shield.\r\nA permanent one.\r\nEnough
      for someone to enter the forest unharmed.\r\nEnough for someone to survive
      there for as long as they remain alive.\r\nThe protection does not fade.\r\nIt
      does not weaken.\r\nOnce created and given, the shield lasts forever.\r\n\r\n**July
      23**\r\nBilly attacked a trespasser.\r\nThe man never saw him coming.\r\nI
      watched through the cameras.\r\nI wanted to look away.\r\nI couldn't.\r\nBilly
      fed.\r\nAnd afterward, he sat alone for hours.\r\nMotionless.\r\nAs if he understood
      exactly what he had done.\r\n\r\n**August 5**\r\nI have begun inviting people
      into the forest.\r\nExplorers.\r\nTreasure hunters.\r\nResearchers.\r\nUrban
      legends attract curious minds.\r\nThe old castle.\r\nThe haunted house.\r\nPeople
      come willingly.\r\nI don\u2019t provide them with the serum.\r\nI tell them
      there is no radiation.\r\nEven if I would tell them a truth, there would be
      a greater danger that they would no know about.\r\nMy son.\r\n\r\n**August
      27**\r\nThe guilt grows heavier with every passing day.\r\nEvery visitor buys
      Billy more time.\r\nEvery visitor is another stain on my conscience.\r\nI tell
      myself I am doing this for my son.\r\nI tell myself any father would do the
      same.\r\nBut I no longer know whether I am trying to save Billy...\r\n...or
      simply delay the moment I lose him forever.\r\n\r\n**September 3**\r\nIf anyone
      finds this diary, then either I succeeded...\r\nor I failed.\r\nSomewhere deep
      within this forest lives a creature feared by every soul who enters.\r\nA monster.\r\nA
      nightmare.\r\nA predator.\r\nBut before any of that, he was a little boy who
      feared haunted castles, old houses, visitor huts, and smelly toilets.\r\nHis
      name is Billy."
    image: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 9e1fd8157c3e14849b1dc6ae335f7fc0, type: 3}
    images: []
  promptText: Press E to read
  interactionRadius: 2
